name: ABC
text: .@GStephanopoulos: "It's hard to summarize in one word or sentence her contributions to American life. But she made her mark on the law, she made her mark on the culture, she made her mark on politics—and she will be remembered for a long time." https://t.co/RvftjpisGI https://t.co/4QgL44P9Zf

name: ABC
text: Ruth Bader Ginsburg, who was sworn in as the second female justice on the Supreme Court in 1993, has passed away at the age of 87. https://t.co/hEatXGl2A7 https://t.co/UPZ06XfuA3

name: ABC
text: JUST IN: Hillary Clinton on the passing of Ruth Bader Ginsburg: "Justice Ginsburg paved the way for so many women, including me. There will never be another like her. Thank you RBG." https://t.co/rzUFgxLCir https://t.co/DII4vxJNUn

name: ABC
text: "She was obviously more than just a Supreme Court Justice, she was an American icon," @jonkarl remembers Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg. https://t.co/sZRl9NoNvS https://t.co/s03IhYifqA

name: ABC
text: JUST IN: Statement from former Pres. George W. Bush on passing of Ruth Bader Ginsburg: "She dedicated many of her 87 remarkable years to the pursuit of justice and equality, and she inspired more than one generation of women and girls." https://t.co/sZRl9NoNvS https://t.co/fTvGEQH3pj

name: ABC
text: Ginsburg had become the standard bearer for the court's liberal wing, writing landmark opinions that advanced gender equality and rights for disabled Americans and immigrants in her more than quarter century on the bench. https://t.co/UuhWIful5w

name: ABC
text: CHILL OUT: A tiger found a way to cool off amid soaring temperatures in Arizona by playing with some blocks of ice in its enclosure at the Phoenix Zoo. https://t.co/sMPbJMdFVJ https://t.co/jvzNyt42K2

name: ABC
text: NEW: Bernie Sanders on passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg: "She was an extraordinary champion of justice and equal rights, and will be remembered as one of the great justices in modern American history." https://t.co/zy982nd1QO https://t.co/4cjgdw92CV

name: ABC
text:
“A gender line… helps to keep women not on a pedestal, but in a cage.” 

-- Ruth Bader Ginsburg in 1975, during oral argument before the Supreme Court in Weinberger v. Wiesenfeld. https://t.co/rzUFgxLCir https://t.co/wzRHHGqanL

name: ABC
text: BREAKING: Pres. Trump is expected to put forth a nominee to fill Ruth Bader Ginsburg's seat in the coming days, multiple sources close to the president and with direct knowledge of the situation tell @ABC News. https://t.co/NpSSjiSOLo

name: ABC
text: Ginsburg was the second woman to sit on the high court, joining Sandra Day O'Connor in 1993, and went on to become its longest-serving woman in history. She was the first female Jewish justice. https://t.co/zy982nd1QO https://t.co/cUjx51Rgra

name: ABC
text: NEW: Sen. Elizabeth Warren on passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg: "The t-shirts simply labeled 'RBG' made her notorious. But it was her wit, her tenaciousness, and her skill as a jurist that made her an icon." https://t.co/Rop1Hlthzf https://t.co/J7jqqCrkzU

name: ABC
text: BREAKING: Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, in statement on passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg, says, "President Trump’s nominee will receive a vote on the floor of the United States Senate." https://t.co/ITHpol2lr5 https://t.co/7ijpnbFv8U
